HBA 4th Annual Family Law Institute
March 30, 2001

8:15am - 8:50am Registration

8:50am - 9:00am Welcome and Opening Remarks
Susan Myres, The Fullenweider Firm
Chair, HBA Family Law Section

9:00am - 9:30am  Is Professionalism Decency?
Hon. Alvin Zimmerman

9:30am - 10:30am It's All Over - Now What? -
Attacking and Defending Rule 11 Agreements, Mediated Settlement Agreements
and Arbitration Awards
Warren Cole, Piro &
Lilly
Richard Orsinger

10:30am - 10:45am Break

10:45am - 11:15am What's So Temporary About Temporary
Orders?
Ellen A. Yarrell, Ellen A. Yarrell, P.C.

11:15am - 12:15pm The Direct and Cross Examination of
a Mental Health Professional
Dr. Jean Guez
Direct examination - Lynn Kamin, Short and Jenkins
Cross examination -  Ray Epps

12:15pm - 1:30pm       Lunch on Your Own

1:30pm - 2:15pm Mock Trial - Enforcing Periods of
Possession: A Demonstration of How (and How Not To) Prove Up Your Case

Presiding Judge - Hon. Doug Warne, 311th District Court
Counsel for Movant -  Alyssa Lemkuil, Harris
County Domestic Relations Office
Movant -  Robert S. Clark, Law Office of Robert S. Clark, P.C.
Counsel for Respondent -  Hon. Robert Hinojosa
Respondent -  Beth Liebling, Attorney at Law

2:15pm - 2:45pm Who Ya Gonna Call When CPS Comes a Knockin?
Linda A. Thompson, Law Office of Linda A. Thompson

2:45pm - 3:00pm Break


3:00pm - 4:00pm  To Move or Not To Move - The
Question of the Millenium
Moderator:   Stewart Gagnon,  Fulbright
and Jaworski
Panelists: Judge Robert Kern, 387th
District Court, Ft. Bend County
Dr. Joan Anderson
Walter P. Mahoney, Law Office of Walter P.
Mahoney, Jr.

4:00pm - 4:30pm  The Utilization of a Financial
Expert
Geoffrey S. Poll, C.P.A., J.D.
Ferguson+Camp+Poll, P.C.


4:30pm - 5:00pm To Grandmother's House We Go: A Look At
Third Party Standing And Rights Of Access
Sallee Smyth, Short and Jenkins


Registration Fees

HBA Members:  Pre-registration:   $90;   Door Registration:   $100

Non-Members:   Pre-registration:   $125;   Door Registration: $150

Note: Pre-registration must be received at the HBA  no later than 12:00
noon, April 5, 2001.
No refunds will be given after that date.

